{"nodes": [{"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_m1_contract", "label": "M1 contract (ContainerBackend + read_workspace)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Binding M1 contract written after the Codex adversarial review; incorporates all 20 findings: exact container profile, run lifecycle, capability probing, read_workspace jail, 14 acceptance criteria, 7-step implementation order."}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d1_writable_workspace", "label": "D1: writable dedicated workspace", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "~/.vestibule/workspace mounted read-write at /workspace: a declared, contained blast radius inside a Vestibule-owned folder, never user data. Rejected read-only+scratch (kills the persistent file output channel) and a per-call workspace_write param (grows the tool surface)."}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d2_pinned_images", "label": "D2: pinned official images, no auto-pull", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "python:3.12-slim (also runs bash) and node:22-slim pinned by digest so image bytes can never silently change. Never pull inside a tool call (multi-minute stall + CLI chatter risk); a missing image returns the exact docker pull command. Rejected custom published image (owning image CI + supply chain too early) and auto-pull at startup (MCP handshake timeout risk)."}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d3_tiered_degradation", "label": "D3: tiered degradation (hard controls block, soft limits degrade)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Hard controls change what hostile code can reach (network none, cap-drop, no-new-privileges, read-only rootfs, non-root user, workspace mount) \u2014 any missing means the run is refused. Soft limits only bound consumption (memory/cpu/pids/tmpfs), all backstopped by the external timeout \u2014 a missing one degrades loudly as container-degraded. Plain 'container' only when the full profile verifiably applied."}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d4_runtime_agnostic", "label": "D4: Docker-first, runtime-agnostic", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The backend never assumes a runtime by name \u2014 it verifies capabilities via probes, so any runtime that passes is safe. VESTIBULE_RUNTIME=auto|docker|podman from day one; only Docker tested in M1, Podman documented as experimental."}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d9_script_mount", "label": "D9: read-only /sandbox script delivery", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Script written to a per-run host temp dir mounted read-only at /sandbox. Not argv (256 KB code blows Windows command-line limits), not stdin (-i is forbidden), not the workspace (would pollute the persistent channel)."}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_container_profile", "label": "Container execution profile (contract section 3)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Exact flag set: network none, cap-drop ALL, no-new-privileges, read-only rootfs, non-root user, mem=swap, cpus, pids-limit, capped tmpfs, no host env inheritance, --rm --init, --pull never, deadline/owner labels. Never present: --privileged, devices, host namespaces, socket mounts, -i/-t."}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_read_workspace_tool", "label": "read_workspace MCP tool", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_read_workspace_jail", "label": "read_workspace path jail", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Guest-planted symlinks are the headline attack. Lexical rejection (.. , absolute paths, any colon/ADS, UNC/device prefixes, NUL, reserved device names, trailing dots/spaces) before touching the filesystem; then a component walk refusing symlinks/reparse points, commonpath containment, O_NOFOLLOW opens. Residual TOCTOU documented, not silently ignored."}, {"id": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_capability_probing", "label": "Backend selection & capability probing (contract section 5)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Lazy, once per process, on first tool call so the MCP handshake is never delayed. Full-profile probe is a real run; on failure retry without soft flags (container-degraded); else every run_code is Blocked with the runtime's own error. Misconfiguration is never silent."}, {"id": "src_vestibule_backends_container_containerbackend", "label": "ContainerBackend", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "One throwaway container per run_code call, driven through the Docker/Podman CLI via asyncio.create_subprocess_exec; container-per-run cold-start cost accepted as M2's benchmark baseline (D5)."}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_container_profile", "target": "docs_history_stdin_devnull_rule", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_m1_contract", "target": "docs_reviews_m1_codex_adversarial_review_codex_review", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_m1_contract", "target": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_container_profile", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_m1_contract", "target": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_capability_probing", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "src_vestibule_backends_container_containerbackend", "target": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_container_profile", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "src_vestibule_backends_container_containerbackend", "target": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d9_script_mount", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "src_vestibule_backends_container_containerbackend", "target": "src_vestibule_backends_base_warden", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.95, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_read_workspace_tool", "target": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_read_workspace_jail", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_read_workspace_tool", "target": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d1_writable_workspace", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_read_workspace_jail", "target": "docs_architecture_pivot_root_jail", "relation": "semantically_similar_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.75, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d3_tiered_degradation", "target": "claude_honest_isolation_reporting", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.95, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_capability_probing", "target": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_d4_runtime_agnostic", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/plans/M1-container-backend.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_reviews_m1_codex_adversarial_review_finding_4_cli_kill", "target": "docs_plans_m1_container_backend_m1_contract", "relation": "rationale_for", "confidence": "EXTRA